  "script": "SCENE 1: TABLETOP SCENE\\nCamera: Wide shot of a softly lit wooden table. A porcelain bowl, chipped and fissured, rests on a felt pad. A warm amber lamp glows in the background.\\nAction: The artisan gathers tools: brushes, urushi lacquer, gold powder, and a clean cloth. He lays the pieces of the bowl in their approximate positions on the workspace.\\nDialogue: Artisan: The past lives in these cracks. We remember by mending.\\n\\nSCENE 2: PREPARATION\\nCamera: Macro on cracked edge; lacquer droplets bead on the surface.\\nAction: He cleans the edges with a soft brush, then dusts the area with a fine cloth. He tests the fit by gently joining two shards.\\nDialogue: Artisan: We do not erase the break; we guide light through it.\\n\\nSCENE 3: LACQUER AND GOLD\\nCamera: Close-up on a brush dipping into lacquer, then into gold powder.\\nAction: The artisan applies thin layers of lacquer to the cracks, then sprinkles gold powder into the wet lines. He uses a delicate touch to sweep away excess powder.\\nDialogue: Artisan: Gold is the seam where resilience becomes beauty.\\n\\nSCENE 4: DRYING AND CURE\\nCamera: Time-lapse of the bowl resting, lacquer drying, light shifting.\\nAction: The pieces settle as the lacquer cures. A faint glow appears along the seams as the gold takes hold.\\nDialogue: Artisan: Patience is part of the craft.\\n\\nSCENE 5: REVEAL\\nCamera: Slow rotation around the finished bowl; soft light glints off the gold lines.\\nAction: The bowl sits on a small wooden stand, now whole and radiant despite its history.\\nDialogue: Artisan: We mend to honor what was broken and to welcome what remains.",
